<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-27 00:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Miss Penn. Named Miss Teen USA  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Jillian Parry, an 18-year-old from
Pennsylvania, was crowned Miss Teen USA 2000 on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Miss Texas, Nicole O'Brian, 17, of Friendswood, was first
runner-up and Miss Kentucky, Kristen Johnson, 18, of Slaughters,
was second runner-up.
</P>
<P>
   Other finalists were Miss Georgia, Abby Vaillancourt, 18, of
Fayetteville, and Miss Tennessee, Casey Porter, 17, of McMinnville.
</P>
<P>
   Teens from all 50 states and the District of Columbia competed
in the contest.
</P>
<P>
   Parry, who wants to study law, won on the merits of her answers
to questions based on the summer CBS hit ''Survivor.'' She got an
animated response from the judges for saying she would prefer to
eat rats over eels.
</P>
<P>
   Parry, of Newtown, was crowned by 1999 Miss Teen USA Ashley
Coleman of Delaware.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
