<DOCNO> APW20000827.0012 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-27 01:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mariners 11, White Sox 5  </HEADLINE>
By JIM COUR
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- The Mariners finally found some offensive pop
again as Alex Rodriguez homered and Mike Cameron had three RBIs to
help Seattle win for just the second time in 13 games, 11-5 over
the Chicago White Sox on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners, held to four singles in a 4-1 loss to the White
Sox on Friday, scored 10 runs in a game for the first time since
Aug. 8.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners increase their lead to 2&AMP;frac12; games over second-place
Oakland in the AL West. The Athletics lost to the New York Yankees
10-6 Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   John Halama (11-6), pitching for the first time in 10 days, gave
up a single to Frank Thomas with two out in the first inning and
then retired 16 straight batters before Tony Graffanino opened the
seventh with a single.
</P>
<P>
   Trailing 7-0, Chicago scored five runs in the seventh on a
two-run double by Paul Konerko, an RBI single by Herbert Perry and
a two-run single by Charles Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners took a 3-0 lead after Rocky Biddle got two outs in
the fourth. Edgar Martinez, John Olerud and Carlos Guillen singled
with Martinez scoring from third on Guillen's hit. After Cameron
walked to load the bases, Joe Oliver had a two-run single.
</P>
<P>
   Seattle made it 5-0 in the fifth on a sacrifice fly by Al Martin
and Rodriguez's team-leading 32nd homer.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners added two more runs in the sixth on an RBI double
by Cameron and Henderson's sacrifice fly to go ahead 7-0.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners added three insurance runs in the seventh on
Guillen's sacrifice fly and Cameron's two-run double. Raul Ibanez
homered in the eighth to make it 11-5.
</P>
<P>
   Halama allowed five runs and five hits in 6 2-3 innings. Biddle
gave up seven runs and nine hits in 5 1-3 innings.
</P>
<P>
Notes: White Sox 2B Ray Durham was ejected by home plate umpire
Tony Randazzo after getting called out on strikes in the ninth
inning. ... The Mariners have been in first place since June 29,
with a record of 27-27 since then. ... Rodriguez homered for the
24th time at Safeco Field. ... In the seventh, the White Sox batted
around for the 28th time this season. ... Thomas struck out for the
sixth time with the bases loaded this year. With the bases loaded,
he also has a homer, double, two singles, two walks and three
sacrifice flies for 12 RBIs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
