<DOCNO> APW20000827.0106 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-27 20:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Odom Put on IR as Bucs Trim Roster  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Tampa Bay hoped Jason Odom would be its
starting left tackle. Instead, Odom will miss the season after
being placed on injured reserve Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Sixteen players were waived, non of them well-known veterans.
Two others were placed on the reserve list with non-football
injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Odom missed all but two days of training camp because of lower
back pain. He started the first three games of 1999 at right
tackle, but sat out the remainder of the year with a back problem
that required surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Confident he would return from his injury, the Bucs signed Odom
to a three-year, $10 million contract in February and planned to
move him from right to left tackle with Paul Gruber's future
uncertain after breaking his right leg in last year's
regular-season finale.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think all of us, including Jason, felt IR was the way to
go,'' coach Tony Dungy said. ''We didn't feel that good about his
prospects of playing real soon.''
</P>
<P>
   With Odom out, the left tackle job belongs to Pete Pierson, who
started two playoff games after Gruber was injured. George Hegamin
will be the backup.
</P>
<P>
   Dungy waived offensive tackles John Blick and Kendall Mack;
defensive linemen Carl Bradley and Chartric Darby; tight ends Jason
Freeman, James Whalen and Henry Lusk; cornerbacks Deshone Mallard
and Earthwind Moreland; wide receivers Daniel Jones, Yo Murphy and
Drew O'Connor; linebacker Bobbie Howard; safety Jeff Popovich; and
running back Ketric Sanford.
</P>
<P>
   Safety Shevin Smith, who dislocated his left big toe in the
third preseason game, was waived after reaching an injury
settlement. Fullback Kevin McLeod was placed on
reserve/non-football illness, and linebacker LB Shawn Stuckey was
put on reserve/non-football injury.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
