<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-27 22:00 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hopson Gets Cut by The 49ers  </HEADLINE>
By ANNE M. PETERSON
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- A little more than a week after he had
emergency gall bladder surgery on a team trip to Seattle, the San
Francisco 49ers waived guard Tyrone Hopson.
</P>
<P>
   Hopson was one of 13 players cut by the 49ers on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Hopson felt ill at the team meal before the Seahawks game on
Aug. 19, and was taken to a local hospital, where gall stones were
discovered. Last week, he said he thought he would be out for about
a month.
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers apparently decided that was too long to wait.
</P>
<P>
   ''We feel he may have a fairly lengthy recovery period,'' 49ers
coach Steve Mariucci said.
</P>
<P>
   There were no big names or real surprises among the others cut
Sunday. They were tight end Shonn Bell, defensive tackle William
Carr, wide receiver Dwight Carter, linebacker Jim Emanuel, wide
receiver Chafie Fields, tackle Dan Goodspeed, safety Ronnie Heard,
defensive back Kelly Herndon, safety Marcus Hill, defensive back
Fred White, fullback Joshua White, and injured linebacker Joe
Wesley.
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers also put tight end Terrence Dupree on injured reserve.
Defensive tackle Jason Tenner was placed on the reserved-left squad
list.
</P>
<P>
   The list was more notable for who the 49ers kept. The team will
carry four quarterbacks, led by starter Jeff Garcia, then Rick
Mirer and draft picks Tim Rattay and Gio Carmazzi.
</P>
<P>
   Carmazzi, the team's third-round pick out of Hofstra, was hailed
as San Francisco's quarterback of the future. But he has been
disappointing in the preseason and slow to pick up the 49ers'
system. Seventh-round pick Rattay, out of Louisiana Tech, has fared
better.
</P>
<P>
   In fact, the 49ers kept all 11 of their draft picks.
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers kept just two tight ends, starter Greg Clark, who has
been nursing a calf injury, and second-year man Justin Swift. That
was to make room for six running backs and the extra quarterback,
Mariucci explained.
</P>
<P>
   ''We are a little heavy, as you know, at quarterback and running
back, which means you have to go short in another area,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Among the running backs, the 49ers retained rookies Paul Smith,
a fifth-round pick who also has been hobbled by a calf injury, and
rookie free agent Jonas Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   ''In a perfect world we don't have to play them this season''
because starter Charlie Garner will handle the job, Mariucci said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-08-27-00 2200 </TRAILER>
